A report of the incident at the 96th Street station near Broadway came in around 3 p.m. MTA officials say a northbound commuter 1 train rear-ended an out-of-service 1 train leading to some kind of a derailment just north of the station on the Upper West Side. The out-of-service 1 train had earlier been vandalized and had workers on it, according to the MTA. At least 24 people were said to have minor injuries in the derailment and taken to area hospitals, according to the FDNY. The passenger train that derailed had approximately 300 people on board and they were evacuated, according to New York City Transit President Richard Davey.
